caption: Our hostess/server was great. Brunch menu is standard fare done well, which is also a plus (who wants to get adventurous at brunch?). Drinks are good and came out fast. Will definitely be back.
Great service, very kind wait employees, and delicious food. I recommend the chicken picante!
Post CV hangout that needs some light.

A complete surprise and a complete pleasure. The service, food, and safety precautions were all incredibly executed. The location was full of sensible people and the atmosphere, while a little cold, was welcoming and delightful. Highly recommend the roasted Brussels Sprouts, perfectly-light-fried-pickles, and the hearty meatballs. So good!
Food was horrible. Glasses were filthy. Overpriced. Will never eat here again.
I Love their food, cocktails and the staff  is very professional and well educated!

We loved eating here when the dining room/patio was open. Great atmosphere, friendly staff, and the food is on point every time. Everything we’ve had so far tastes like it was made with care just for you. Great beer selection too! Delivery has been equally delicious! Quick, hot, and the fries were the crispiest fries I’ve ever eaten.

Brunch is pretty mediocre. We got the breakfast poutine and morning fix. It's just a lot of ingredients on a plate (e.g. potatoes) without much cohesiveness. Egg benedict on French toast is very weird. Don't do it.

Woah... super delicious. We went for Brunch and had a perfect time. The $12 bottomless Mimosas is hard to beat 😅 they were quick with the refills too. The food was scrumptious. I pleasantly stuffed afterwards. They treat the COVID guidelines with respect as well.
Sat on the patio....they were jamming both inside and out!  Really tasty food and easy to order.  Server definitely running hard to keep up.  Great beverage selections

Great service! Our waitress was the very nice lady with the "Don't Panic" tattoo! Over 400 whiskeys to choose from and she was spot on with knowledge and able to serve me, the best whiskey I've ever had.  Great food! Best whiskeys! Thank you for being our server that day!
Visited at eight, it was not full.
Great for and drink
Cheese curds, fried pickles, a meatball sub setup with a pile of booze. If you don’t like this place you ain’t LIVIN I’ll tell you

I have gone to Monkeys Paw from nearly the day they opened. It has always been so well run and designed. It is like the pub equivalent of the iPhone.  So, not surprisingly,  they have designed a safe, delicious, outside dining experience.
HAWT FYAH

The menu and atmosphere here are wonderful, but I continue coming back as they have some of the best cheese curds in the city! I've never been disappointed with any of the food here, and they have a great drink menu as well.
Love this place!
Great service and very good food. We also liked the atmosphere

This place has some of the best food I've ever had. Real good farm to table content right here! Try their chicken sandwich. They basically put the entire chicken on there and it's just amazing. Bottomless mimosas on Sunday with some biscuits and gravy. Lord have mercy! LOVE!

Went here with a friend and as always I had a great time! Their food is very good and it’s a cute spot and location. Their Brussels spouts are great! Also, loved the meatball sandwich. I recommend! Their grilled cheese isn’t out of this world, but it’s good. I don’t think I’d pay that much for it, but it is what it is.
Great food, value for money

Breakfast poutine is such an amazing indulgence (it's a lot, so be prepared).  It's not the cheapest option yet I've seen higher prices. The biggest issue is their mimosa "deal". I only wanted two and it was more expensive than had I just done the bottomless option. How much sense does that make?  I like the ambiance.  I'll be back to try and rectify this mimosa deal.
Small but delicious menu, and flexible kitchen that's willing to swap things out to make it vegetarian!
Such good food! Very nice ambiance.
The food is awesome!
The Monkeys Paw is a nice place! I live by and enjoy Bear games there. Robin is great behind the bar!!

The overall service and ambiance is awesome. The Spirits are top notch. The food is not good at all. I understand they have a Chef that has worked a lot of places. He should just bow out before this place is ruined. I had the opportunity to eat and drink here again and it was a hard pass. Just get a new chef the one you have is a disaster.

While it kinda just looks like a regular neighborhood bar from the outside, once inside you'll find a cozy and low key gastropub with a seasonal menu, unique draft list, and even more extensive whiskey selection.  We shared the fresh burrata & citrus beets to start, which were fantastic! Loved the citrus bits and as a collective bite, each ingredient complimented each other so well! For entrees, I did the Monkey's Paw Burger ~ two patties, american cheese, balsamic onions, butter pickles, aoili and served with a side of fries. Excellent. I'm becoming more convinced Chicago should be known for their burgers. My wife had the braised pork ragu which was yummy as well from the few bites I stole.  On some other visits, I've also tried the shishito peppers, brussel sprouts, fish & chips, and a seasonal chicken piccata. Anyways, nothing but praise for this one. They do take reservations if you're looking to lock something down. It actually makes for a nice, low key date night spot.  'Til next time!

Honesty kind of over priced for what I feel like we got.  The food was good but not amazing  The atmosphere is was really cool  I liked it but I don’t suspect I’ll be back with so many other options in this city  Worth a trip inside for a beer to make your own opinion

This place is reasonably priced compared to other brunch places in Chicago, we went on a Sunday during brunch/lunch and it was  a pretty calm atmosphere. Food was good. Not overcrowded at all. The only thing is our waitress was not so attentive. Ignored us most of the time, to the point that we had to get up and walk the bill+payment to her so we could get going. I don't get the vibe that this is standard for this place, but still, it was kind of annoying for a place that forces you to tip a certain amount.
Good food, good drink selection. Terrible service. Expect to sit at the bar for at least 10 minutes before the bartender walks over
Great vibe. Great food. Great people. Amazing grilled cheese!

(Translated by Google) It is a very nice atmosphere, the friendly staff, I like the food of the Chef Aracely Cuevas and the dishes shine of clean, there is water for pets during the day.  (Original) Es un ambiente muy agradable el personal amable, me gusta la comida de la Chef Aracely Cuevas y los platos brillan de limpios, hay agua para mascotas durante el día.
Take this review with a grain of salt. I stayed for 2 beers. But the bathrooms were clean, it was a nice vibe, and the draughts were really good. Definitely worth visiting again for proper meal.
Great rotating beer selection! They also have really good food with a friendly and knowledgeable owner and staff. This was the first bar to introduce me to Pipeworks Brewing.
Great place.
Always friendly bartenders. My go to spot!
Great whiskey selection and craft cocktails.
Best whiskey selection in Lincoln park!
Good whiskey, service was just okay
The muscles are generous and delicious. Half price wine Wednesday!
Delicious food, extensive whisky list, and great wait staff. Will be back!

A pretty fun place but you also pay for it. I ate there once literally in the first few weeks when they opened but haven't done so since so I honestly can't recall much about the "Gastro" portion of their offerings. However, they offer a comprehensive selection of whiskey.
Amazing brunch
Drinks weren't really that great. Tried two and was dissapointing in both one of which was an old fashioned...should be a fairly easy drink to make
This place is AMAZING I’m here at least 3 times a week!

Servers and host are indifferent, wait time for our brunch was too long (60 mins) considering the place was half empty. The coffee which I had hoped would at least be good was awful, we were asked if we wanted a refill once and that was right before we left. The prices do not justify the amount and taste of the food that you get. The ambience is nice but that's about the only nice thing about this place.
One of our favorite spots for a great cocktail and meal!

The food was decent but the wait time was horrible. Took 50 min of waiting for our brunch ( we were total of 3 people  in the table). Thry also screwed up one of the orders , they did give it complimentary since they screwed up. I want to give it 4 but the wait time was a pain.
Solid brunch option. Good food and mimosas.
Upscale little bar with really good food.   The brussel sprouts we're really yummy as well as the pork.The menu and I appreciate selection changes frequently but the food is always yummy.
cool place, but it gets so crowded always! Food very good and interesting seasonal menu plus cool cocktails and big craft beer list. service is reasonably good during their busy times
Great staff and great food
Great for groups!
it's good service and atmosphere

I was surprised how much I ended up liking this place. Stopping here was a total impulse. My wife and I were driving around looking for a new place to try and noticed The Monkey's Paw. The inside is much nicer than the outside alludes. The drinks were well priced, the food was awesome, and the staff was very friendly. I'm very happy we stopped in and we'll definitely be back.
Excellent coffee, fantastic cheese curds, and some of the best chilaquilles around.  Great bloody mary, too.

Food is very good and they have a nice cocktail menu.  Nice ambiance too.  For a neighborhood place, though, they could be a lot more friendly.  The bartender took his time wandering over to us and barely said a word, but even small talk. the hostess was indifferent and did not smile.  (We had the sames experience last time we were here.)  We made a 7:00 reservation a couple weeks ago and were seated immediately outside the restrooms, which are open to the dining area.  (They ready should reconfigure that.)  With so many other options in the area, I doubt we'll be back.
Good food, and recently returned to have a drink near the fireplace with HS!
Nice quiet bar.  Cozy seating by the fireplace.
Amazing selection of spirits and great service.
Great food,great service!
Good wine list, nice atmosphere. Best Brussel sprouts ever.
Order the brussel sprouts, soft pretzel, and meatballs. A+
Good brunch options and friendly staff. And the grilled cheese sandwich (served with tomato basil soup) was very tasty!
Mediocre, nice space but overpriced.  Food just ok.
Awesome whiskey menu. Came here for a birthday party. The staff were awesome, and very knowledgeable.
Nice quaint place! Wednesday's are half off bottles of wine! They have great food too
Good food,great atmosphere.
So so chicken bisquit sandwich and michelada.
If you like cheese, there are a lot of cheese options... Cheese curds for appetizer, meatballs with cheese curds, and an amazing grilled cheese sandwich. #cheese
Love this place. Great atmosphere and consistently good food.
Good food selection. Plenty of wine and beer to choose from. Nice place to meet up with friends.

This place has a wonderful brunch selection. The bottomless mimosas were reasonably priced and the food was delicious. I got the breakfast flatbread, and it was so unique and wonderful. The atmosphere was also so cool. Definitely check it out.

The food and ambiance are great, as is the wine list and the prices are very reasonable (especially on Wednesdays--1/2 off). The service was great--Paul is such a good bartender that some might call him a STARtender:)
Great food, great atmosphere in a relaxed part of town. Happy hour hangout in a relaxed atmosphere. The menu is diverse and fulfilling.
Lovely atmosphere, great neighborhood, and good food. The menu is small so you know they care about quality. The drink menu is excellent and they have unique stuff. Very classy
Great atmosphere and menu at this neighborhood bar.
Good cocktails. Interesting, unique space. Friendly staff.
My boyfriend and I frequent here because we love it! Great neighborhood spot that’s date-worthy! Warm, intimate and their entire menu can be shared.
Good food and service
Not a dive bar nor 'bro bar.  Great bar service and drink selection.
Great drinks
Great ambiance!

A quaint neighborhood pup and restaurant. I've only been here for brunch and drinks, but I was impressed with the diversity and novelty of the brunch menu considering how unassuming the restaurant is as a whole. I will be back.

Got a few apps, all we're pretty good. Cocktails are great. Decent, not the greatest, beer selection. Supposed to be a great brunch spot but I haven't tried it. Service was fine.

I've been here a few times.  They have good food and drinks. Poutine, sloppy joe sliders,  meatballs,  burger are all very good. But the star of the show for me has always been their Brussels sprouts.  So crispy and yummy!
Great food at good prices. Service a little slow but will worth the trip.
Most of the beers we ordered the taps were out but they had sports on TV and other beers that weren't out that.

Service was great. Drinks were good. Food was very disappointing.  Poutine was so salty it was almost inedible. The monkey bread actually was inedible. It was covered in vinegar, which was not mentioned anywhere on the menu.  I will not return to eat here but the drink and whiskey selection are worth a visit.

Found this place for Restaurant Week based on location and their drink selection, and my expectations were far exceeded. Farm to table fare, and everything was delicious. The prix fix, three course meal for $33 was outstanding, and the waiter was not only pleasant and personable, but extremely helpful to pair wine and beer with our food selections.

The restaurant specializes is local, farm-to-table, seasonal foods.  Everything is incredible and, because it is seasonal, hits the spot.  Also has a great wine, beer, and whiskey selection (with whiskey and wine flights).  The staff is always friendly.
Lovely food. Wonderful service. Brunch here is awesome, and the menu changes regularly.

Scotch scotch scotch, into my belly. Food is great and the scotch selection is better. Awesome for tinder dates or people that like to watch awkward tinder dates from the corner of their eye. Fireplace and books so you can feel smart and comfy through osmosis! Ask the bartender to show you a magic trick, I don't think they know any but it will be funny if everyone asks them. Maybe they will learn magic and pull quarters out of your ear, ask enough times and you will have unlimited money to pay your tab!
Awesome whiskey selection and a great burger. The food menu is a bit small, but each item has a unique twist.

You really cannot go wrong with Monkey's Paw. Now that Rose Angeli's is dead and gone, it wears the crown as ruler of food in the area. The food is magnificent and the beer is out of this world. If you want something a little different beer wise, ask for the bottle list which has beers that are hard or impossible to find elsewhere.
Fantastic drink selection and decent food.
Solid drinks - good prices.

A laid back classy bar. With a knowledgeable bar staff about Beers, Wines and the largest Whiskey collection from all over the world in Lincoln Park. The wooden decor added to the atmosphere as I sat down to one of the tastiest meals I've ever had from the inventive chef's menu. For example The chef's has reinvented meatballs. Something I didn't think I'd care about until I tasted them, they in particular are like no other and stupendous. This is indicative of the food menu both classic and new tastes to enjoy. There are only a few TV screen's. So that neon light doesn't bathe the bar during any given game that must be watched and the sound is lower so you can still have a conversation. I have had many a good conversation with both staff and clientele alike.
Excellent food! Had dinner there and also brunch. Strongly recommend them. Make a nice bloody mary!
Great selection of scotch and whiskey.
Excellent customer service. Great food and whiskey selection

This is a true neighborhood gem. Tucked away in Lincoln Park, this spot offers over 200 different types of Whiskey, a great craft beer selection from midwest breweries such as Pipeworks and Spiteful, and locally sourced dishes prepared by Chef Rah Shabazz.  Sunday brunch is outstanding, definitely grab a Bloody Mary (decorated with a grilled green onion, pickled pineapple, sharp cheddar cheese and salami) and try "The Morning Fix" (maple vanilla french toast, sausage, poached eggs, hollandaise sauce and maple syrup) it's AMAZING.  The Monkey's paw is a great date spot (ask to sit in the Library) and they also can accommodate large groups for special occasions.

This is a great restaurant that serves farm to table. The menu changes often and is always delicious but the variety of liqueur and beer is always there. There are plenty of options for everyone and the atmosphere is one that cannot be beat.

The restaurant itself is tucked away into a nondescript building of the Lincoln Park neighborhood. This cozy gastropub with its dim lighting, wooden dark furniture and a faux fireplace provides for a pleasant experience. It’s definitely a go-to spot for those who live nearby. The service is friendly and polite from the minute you walk through the door. Last time I was there with a group of girlfriends, we chatted, laughed and forgot about the time. We overstayed the restaurant opening hours by at least half an hour but no one from the staff tried to rush us off by taking away our unfinished plates or bringing us the check before we were ready to go. The waiter just kept coming to our table politely asking if we wanted to order anything else.

Easily one of the all-time BEST BRUNCHES in the city of Chicago. My friend and I were both blown away by the food and the drinks as were the two people sitting at the table next to us. Chef Rah throws down in the kitchen like no one I know. And what's so amazing is he is still so young. If I weren't in public and if I weren't a lady I promise I would have licked my plate clean. That's how good Rah's food tastes.  My friend and I started out with the Bloody Mary which was by far also one of the absolute BEST Bloody Mary's I've ever tasted! It was incredible. Everything about the drink was perfection - the garnish, the amazing bacony rim (did I mention I really don't eat meat but oh so good), and most especially the actual drink itself (base and mix). I could've easily downed a few of these babies... that good. Though I was also intrigued by their whiskey flight which I am going to have to enjoy on my next visit. Yes, there will definitely be a next visit.  For the food, my friend ordered the Rah's Skillet which was beyond delicious. I had my heart set on Ashely's Morning Fix but unfortunately the bread guy never showed that was not an option. I will have it on my return visit. I ended up going with the shrimp and grits.  I had my heart set on getting a side of grits anyways because the menu calls them Chef Rah's special grits and this girl lived in Georgia for a few years where I eventually fell in love with cheesy good grits and have had a really hard time finding here in Chicago. Oh man, Rah's grits are out of this world AMAZING!!!! And the rest of the dish was just as incredibly delicious..... and let me mention there is meat in there. I had to do it.... I didn't want to upset the chef and ask him to prepare his dish differently as it is quite obvious this man knows his way around the kitchen and pairs certain ingredients together for a reason.  Let me just say that if meat tasted that good ALL the time, I'd probably eat it regularly. Everything about Monkey's Paw was amazing and it certainly didn't hurt that chef Rah visited our table to say hi and see how everything was. Both my friend and I cannot wait to return and from posting a few pics from our brunch we have more friends that will be joining us when we do. Trust me, you NEED to put Monkey's Paw on your brunch list and from what I hear dinner is just as amazing.  Chef Rah - You've got a new fan!

caption: One of my favorite places in Chicago...the beer menu caters to local brewers...I've had beers here that I've NEVER seen at any other establishment.  The staff (Casey) is friendly & knowledgable about the beer list as it tends to change out on a regular basis.  Food is awesome...definitely try the mac-n-cheese and whatever flatbread they are serving that night (some of the ingredients may sound strange...but I've never been disappointed).

We wanted to try eats beyond the confines of downtown touristy area and head Northward into the Lincoln Park neighborhoods. This cozy beer/gastropub with dark wood was pleasant. The service was friendly and easy going. We were seated in the nook with a faux fireplace.  The food highlight local and seasonal ingredients. We wanted to try the special flatbread with pulled pork and BBQ sauce. I think the table really enjoyed this. The sauce was tangy and slightly spicy the pork was tender and not overly seasoned. I went for the burger with a side of Poutine fries. You don’t see Poutine much in the states unless you go to Canada so I had to order it.  The Gnocchi was another dish ordered. It was light and fluffy and didn't feel heavy.  We really enjoyed the food and service here. Actually, I can certainly get use to service like this compared to NYC.

Went on a Sunday for brunch. Staff was pretty slow and it wasn't super busy. The side of bacon was weak: $4 for two slices that were the size of one slice uif combined. Yogurt parfait didn't have whole fruit it was like jam or purée. Friends liked the bloody Marys though.

This place is easily one of my favorite local restaurants. The staff is friendly, the food is great, and they have an excellent tap list. The outdoor seating is perfect for brunch or dinner. Best of all, it's relatively undiscovered so you generally don't have to wait for a table!

I have been here several times for dinner and always had a good experience.  Today, I went for Father's Day Brunch and had the best meal so far.  I had the omelet with mushrooms, swiss, and caramelized onions. I also had a taste of the french toast which was really good.  I highly recommend this place.

Had a fantastic time at The Monkey's Paw. Went on a date night w/ the wife and we really enjoyed ourselves. The food was excellent and the atmosphere was very laid-back (e.g. you could have a conversation because there were not 100 TV's within an inch of your face).  Loved it and wil go back...

Monkey's Paw:  Overall A.  Went on a Friday night around 6 PM.  We are early eaters although in our early 30's.  There wasn't a wait for a table, but by 7 the restaurant had filled out nicely.  There is a great menu for craft beers, great wine selection, and spirits as well.  Draft beer selection included beers from Wisconsin, Michigan (Greenbush) and Chicago master brewers.  We had a cheese plate (3 choices for $11) and it came with house parmigiana cracker-bread.  All cheese choices were greeted by, "Oh, wow that's good."  We also ordered the olives.  Not as warm as we would have liked, but great choices of olives in a single serving jar with lid (presentation only).  Both appetizers were great and were nicely paired with our drinks.  For dinner we shared the fish-n-chips.  With a house-made batter, it was light and crispy and cooked perfectly.  It was reasonably priced, $12 for two pieces that were fair-sized.  The desserts offered were great as well, there was an assortment, but we chose only one to share: cherry-infused chocolate mousse.  It was very light and not overly sweet.  The atmosphere was relaxed, a place like this in NYC would have had twice as many tables and packed to the gills, but offered the same food.  Service was fast and friendly-joking with me as we complimented the menu.  We will be back soon as there is no other place like it in the neighborhood.  (One might argue that 404 Wine Bar could be similar, yes, but they don't meet the food quality and excellent service that the Monkey's Paw has to offer.)  Keep it up Monkey's Paw!
Good food, nice varied menu, service sometimes good, sometimes really poor. Excellent selection of craft beers

Right near DePaul and Lincoln Park, The Monkey's Paw is an awesome new place which seems like they've been a local establishment for years.  With rotating taps featuring local and favorite brews, you will discover a new beer for whatever your palette loves.  Have I mentioned the wall of scotches?  Yes, they have a wall stocked of a very impressive collection and assortment of scotches.  Not a beer or scotch fan?  They've got wine to please anyone's fancy.  Can't decide what to drink?  That's OK, they do flights as well.  And the Food!  If you're not the imbibing type, come and enjoy the diverse and delicious menu, crafted by a master chef.  A dish can be had by anyone and accomodate any allergies you may or may not have.  The staff is friendly and treat you like a human being.  Everyone knows what they're talking about and the staff in the back works harder than elves on Christmas Eve.  To show your appreciation for your savory meal, you can opt to buy a 6-pack for the kitchen staff (to enjoy after hours, of course)!  I could go on and on about this place, but I'll shut up and let you decide for yourself.  If you go and are not pleased, please feel free to write me and tell me why you respectfully disagree.  Enjoy.
